### Global Variables
@host = http://localhost:8080
@api = /api/drivers

### 0. Login (to get accessToken)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "max@mustermann.de",
  "password": "securePassword123"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("accessToken", response.body.data.accessToken);
%}

### 1. Create a new Driver with PERCENTAGE_SHARE CONFIG
POST {{host}}{{api}}
Content-Type: application/json
Cookie: accessToken={{accessToken}}

{
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Doe",
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "phone": "+43 664 1234567",
  "remunerationConfig": {
    "remunerationModelType": "PERCENTAGE_SHARE",
    "minDriverPayout": "60",
    "driverRevenueSharePercentage": "60"
  }
}

### Create a new Driver with WEEKLY_FIXED_RATE CONFIG
POST {{host}}{{api}}
Content-Type: application/json
Cookie: accessToken={{accessToken}}

{
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Weekly",
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "phone": "+43 664 1234567",
  "remunerationConfig": {
    "remunerationModelType": "WEEKLY_FIXED_RATE",
    "weeklyFixedRate": "600"
  }
}

### 2. Get All Drivers (Paginated)
GET {{host}}{{api}}?page=0&size=10
Cookie: accessToken={{accessToken}}

### 3. Get Driver by ID
# Replace '1' with a valid driver ID from the response of #2
GET {{host}}{{api}}/1
Cookie: accessToken={{accessToken}}

### 4. Update Driver
PATCH {{host}}{{api}}/1
Content-Type: application/json
Cookie: accessToken={{accessToken}}

{
  "firstName": "John Updated",
  "phone": "+43 664 9999999"
}

### 5. Delete Driver
DELETE {{host}}{{api}}/1
Cookie: accessToken={{accessToken}}
